corresponding legal actions, in order to combat impunity (Ecuador); 
</b></p>
<p><b> </b>102.36.<b> Widen the mandate of the Parliamentary Ombudsman to address 
racial discrimination in public and private entities (Sierra Leone); 
</b></p>
<p><b> </b>102.37.<b> Revise the mandate of the Parliamentary Ombudsman to enable it to 
address racial discrimination in the private sphere and not just racial 
discrimination involving the government and State entities (Nigeria); 
</b></p>
<p><b> </b>102.38.<b> Work towards enhancing the status, powers and functions of the 
office of the Ombudsman to ensure full compliance with the Paris Principles 
